# Page Headers

Always use `<PageHeader>` from `@/components/page-header` for page titles. Never write raw `<h1>` tags.

Header actions use the button primitives from `@/components/ui/button` directly — `LinkButton` for navigation CTAs and `Button` for form submits. (The old `PrimaryButton`/`PrimaryLinkButton` wrappers have been removed.)

```tsx
import { PageHeader } from '@/components/page-header';
import { Button, LinkButton } from '@/components/ui/button';
import { PlusIcon } from '@/components/ui/icons';

// List page with "New" action
<PageHeader
  title="Strategies"
  subtitle="Multi-step workflows that chain generations together."
  actions={<LinkButton href="/strategies/new" iconLeft={<PlusIcon className="size-4" />}>New Strategy</LinkButton>}
/>

// Detail/edit page with back link
<PageHeader
  backHref={`/strategies/${id}`}
  backLabel={`Back to ${name}`}
  title="Edit Strategy"
/>

// Create/edit form page — title="" hides the h1, save button in actions
<PageHeader
  backHref="/input-presets"
  backLabel="Back to Input Presets"
  title=""
  actions={
    <Button onClick={handleCreate} disabled={!canCreate} loading={creating}>
      Create Input Preset
    </Button>
  }
/>
```

- `title` renders as `<h1 className="text-display text-text-primary">` (empty string hides it)
- `subtitle` accepts `React.ReactNode` — use JSX for rich subtitles with links
- `backLabel` defaults to "Back" when omitted
- `actions` slot goes on the right side of the header row
- Use `LinkButton` for navigation CTAs (pass `iconLeft={<PlusIcon className="size-4" />}` for the plus affordance)
- Use `Button` for form submit buttons (`onClick`, `disabled`, `loading`)
